00:16:02,470 --> 00:16:09,968
And then here, whether in 
dollars or euros,

241
00:16:09,968 --> 00:16:14,622
it is the cost of the standard norm.

242
00:16:15,460 --> 00:16:22,100
And then, this is the income 
of the population.

243
00:16:22,100 --> 00:16:26,724
We see that between 
this standard, this norm,

244
00:16:26,724 --> 00:16:32,458
and income, there is 
a gap, a differential,

245
00:16:33,565 --> 00:16:38,176
and this differential should 
be taken into account,

246
00:16:38,176 --> 00:16:40,710
by public authorities.

247
00:16:43,130 --> 00:16:49,925
This differential, is aid to 
the most modest households.

248
00:16:49,925 --> 00:16:54,487
There are two possibilities 
to fill this gap.

249
00:16:58,511 --> 00:17:01,867
There is the possibility 
of offering assistance,

250
00:17:03,517 --> 00:17:06,159
or assisting those who ask for it.

251
00:17:07,099 --> 00:17:13,214
To offer assistance means 
to price land modestly.

252
00:17:13,214 --> 00:17:17,179
We can develop the land 
without being paid for it.

253
00:17:17,179 --> 00:17:19,963
We can build at moderate prices.

254
00:17:19,963 --> 00:17:21,704
This is what will go on the market.

255
00:17:21,704 --> 00:17:26,265
One can offer aid as materials or land.

256
00:17:26,265 --> 00:17:32,028
Aid on demand is based on a system 
of borrowing and spending.

257
00:17:32,028 --> 00:17:37,212
On assists with borrowing, for example,

258
00:17:37,212 --> 00:17:42,820
with a 0% financing, or lowered rates, 
